description: India's Test tour of England marks a generational shift as KL Rahul, Yashasvi Jaiswal, and Shubman Gill shoulder the batting responsibilities in the absence of Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli. Rahul aims for consistency, while Jaiswal faces his biggest challenge yet.
title: Ind vs Eng: Without Virat and Rohit, who will be India's best bet with bat?

author: TNN
description: Karnataka's ban on bike taxis is now in effect following a High Court order. Rapido has paused its bike taxi services, introducing 'Bike Parcel' instead. Transport Minister Ramalinga Reddy warned of strict action against non-compliant aggregators. While Uber and Ola continued offering bike taxi services, the Transport Department maintains that using private vehicles for commercial purposes is illegal
title: K'taka Bike taxi ban: Rapido says it 'paused' services; Ola, Uber continue

author: HIJAM RAJU SINGH
description: The 2021 India-England Test series saw intense battles and a rare disruption, with the final Test delayed by a year due to COVID-19. It resumed in 2022, ending 2-2, and remains a symbol of resilience amid global uncertainty.
title: The series that lasted a year: Why India's 2021 tour of England was halted midway

author: TOI Education
description: Telangana State Board of Intermediate Education released TS Inter Supplementary Results 2025. The results are available on tgbie.cgg.gov.in and results.cgg.gov.in. Students can check results using hall ticket number. Supplementary exams occurred from May 22 to May 29. The marks memo can be downloaded from the website. It contains student details and subject-wise marks.
title: TS Inter Supplementary results for 1st, 2nd year released: Check link to download marks memo

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A recent government report suggests that numerous UFO sightings in the US may be attributed to military disinformation campaigns and covert operations rather than extraterrestrial encounters. The All-domain Anomaly Resolution Office (AARO) uncovered strategies used since the Cold War, including staged evidence and misleading briefings, to obscure classified aircraft programs.
title: UFO sightings in US: New report reveals truth behind the surge; a human-made disinformation

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: Actor Ram Kapoor has recently acquired a Lamborghini Urus SE, priced at Rs 4.57 crore. This plug-in hybrid SUV boasts an impressive 800 hp and can reach 100 kmph in just 3.4 seconds. The Urus SE features design updates, a new infotainment screen, and joins Kapoor's collection of luxury vehicles like Porsche and Ferrari.
title: Actor Ram Kapoor buys Lamborghini Urus SE SUV worth Rs 4.57 crore: See details

description: While head coach Gautam Gambhir was away, India’s assistant coaches Sitanshu Kotak, Ryan ten Doeschate, and Morne Morkel took charge of the team for a four-day intra-squad game against India A in Beckenham.
title: Gautam Gambhir set to rejoin Team India on June 17 in England

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction today: Amidst Israel-Iran tensions, gold prices have surged, crossing ₹1 lakh in India, driven by safe-haven demand. Escalating conflict overshadowed positive US-China trade talk news and strong US jobs data. Traders are closely monitoring Middle East developments for further influence on gold's trajectory.
title: Gold rate outlook for June 16 week amid Israel-Iran conflict- buy or sell?

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Tata Group is establishing India's first semiconductor fabrication facility in Dholera, Ahmedabad. Gujarat is supporting the project by building residential accommodations for Tata employees and vendors. The project includes 1,500 residential units, a fire station, school, hospital and desalination plant. The first chip production is expected by December 2026.
title: India’s 1st semiconductor unit: Gujarat enables 1,500 apartments; mainly for Tata Group staff

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: An Air India Boeing 787 Dreamliner, flight AI-315, en route to Delhi from Hong Kong, was compelled to return to Hong Kong airport on Monday morning due to a suspected technical malfunction detected mid-air.
title: Mid-air scare: Air India's Delhi-bound flight returns to Hong Kong; technical snag suspected

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Elon Musk ignited speculation with a cryptic post, "No gods or kings, only man," shared amidst anti-Trump protests and the anniversary of the US Army. He later reiterated the phrase alongside a SpaceX Starship test video, potentially emphasising human achievement and individual empowerment. The phrase originates from a video game, linked to themes of human autonomy.
title: ‘No Gods or Kings’: Musk posts cryptic message — Here’s the video game that inspired it

title: 'Pak will nuke Israel if...': Top Iranian official; Can Shaheen-3 reach Tel Aviv?

description: ICC chief Jay Shah attended the MLC 2025 doubleheader, meeting franchise owners, ex-cricketers, and stakeholders including Anil Kumble and Adam Gilchrist. He also engaged with CSK CEO Kasi Viswanathan and KKR’s Venky Mysore, highlighting growing global interest in the league.
title: Photos: ICC chief Jay Shah attends MLC double-header at Oakland Coliseum

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Blaise Metreweli, a Cambridge University alumna with a distinguished career in intelligence, has been appointed as the first female head of MI6. Succeeding Richard Moore, she will assume the role in the autumn. Her appointment comes at a crucial time, as the UK faces unprecedented threats, highlighting the vital importance of intelligence services.
title: UK appoints first woman to head spy agency MI6: Meet real-life 'M' character; Who is Blaise Metreweli?

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US Embassy in Israel sustained minor damage due to Iranian missile strikes near its Tel Aviv branch, confirmed the US Ambassador. While no injuries were reported among US personnel, the embassy and consulate will remain closed due to the ongoing security situation.
title: US embassy damaged in Israel: Iran missiles strike Tel Aviv; comes after Trump's warning

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Preparations are underway to conduct the last rites of former Gujarat Chief Minister Vijay Rupani, who tragically died in a plane crash in Ahmedabad last week. His mortal remains will be handed over to his family in Ahmedabad and then transported to Rajkot for the final rites, which will be performed with full state honors at 5 pm.
title: Ahmedabad plane crash: Vijay Rupani's last rites today; to be held with state honours

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Amitabh Kant, a retired IAS officer, concludes his 45-year public service career, stepping down as India's G20 Sherpa. He expressed gratitude to the Prime Minister for the opportunity to contribute to India's development through initiatives like Make in India and Startup India. Kant now aims to support India's progress by working with startups and academic institutions.
title: Amitabh Kant resigns as G20 Sherpa after 45 years in govt service

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Kuldeep Yadav briefly posted a photo with fiancée Vanshika after their June 4 engagement in Lucknow, only to delete it soon after. While fans speculated the reason, the spinner remains focused on India's upcoming Test series in England starting June 20.
title: Post deleted! Kuldeep Yadav shares photos with fiancée Vanshika, later removes it

author: ARVIND CHAUHAN
description: A Saudia aircraft arriving in Lucknow from Jeddah experienced a smoke incident in its landing gear upon arrival on Sunday. Prompt action by the Airport Rescue and Fire Fighting team and the Saudia crew ensured the safe deboarding of all passengers, primarily Haj pilgrims. A minor hydraulic oil leak in the landing gear is suspected to be the cause.
title: Watch: Smoke scare on Saudia Haj flight triggers emergency landing at Lucknow airport

author: GAURAV GUPTA
description: India will face Pakistan in Colombo on October 5 during the 2025 Women’s ODI World Cup, hosted by India and Sri Lanka. The marquee clash follows a hybrid model due to political tensions, with Pakistan’s matches held in neutral Sri Lanka.
title: Women’s WC 2025: Ind vs Pak date confirmed; here’s all you need to know

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations:Motilal Oswal Financial Services recommends Home First Finance and Kaynes as top stock picks for the week starting June 16, 2025. HomeFirst is focusing on emerging states and leveraging technology, expecting lower borrowing costs and NIM expansion. Kaynes Technologies is expanding into high-tech sectors, targeting USD 1 billion revenue by FY28 with significant growth in revenue, EBITDA, and PAT.
title: Buy or sell: Stock recommendations for the week - check list

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: Vance Boelter, 57, has been apprehended in connection with the fatal shooting of Minnesota State Representative Melissa Hortman and her husband, Mark. He is also accused of wounding State Senator John A. Hoffman and his wife.
title: 'Had 70 potential targets': Minnesota shooting suspect arrested; pic released

author: RICHA PINTO
description: Mumbai experienced heavy rainfall on June 16, 2025, with the city area receiving the highest intensity. Wadala recorded the highest rainfall at 161.4 mm, followed by Matunga at 147.55 mm. Bandra in the western suburbs saw 134.59 mm, while Chembur led the eastern suburbs with 111 mm.
title: Heavy showers lash Mumbai; Wadala, Colaba record highest rainfall in 24 hours

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Karun Nair, poised for a Test comeback after eight years, revealed a senior Indian cricketer once urged him to retire for league riches. Defying advice, Nair's domestic dominance and resilience earned him a spot in India’s squad for England Tests.
title: IND vs ENG: Karun Nair – 'A prominent Indian cricketer advised me to retire'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Tensions escalate as Israel and Iran exchange missile strikes, defying global calls for de-escalation. Israeli airstrikes inside Iran targeted nuclear and energy sites, resulting in over 230 deaths. Iran retaliated with missile barrages, causing casualties and damage in Israel. Nuclear talks are suspended amidst fears of wider regional conflict, with both sides signaling no immediate end to hostilities.
title: Israel-Iran trade blows; IDF targets weapon mfg sites - Key developments

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Amidst escalating Israel-Iran tensions, Indian students in Iran are pleading with the Indian government for evacuation, citing safety concerns due to recent aerial attacks near residential areas. Students describe being jolted awake by explosions and express fear for their survival, especially with restricted airspace complicating their return home.
title: 'Not slept in 3 days': Fear grips Indian students in Iran amid Israel tensions

author: ARANI BASU
description: Bharat Arun emphasizes the potential of India's bowling attack for the England tour, highlighting Arshdeep Singh and Akash Deep. He urges bowlers to step up in Bumrah's absence and focus on match-to-match plans, stressing consistency and partnership bowling.
title: ‘Share Bumrah’s workload’; Former India bowling coach Bharat Arun

description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Monday. While Nifty50 was above 24,750, BSE Sensex rose over 200 points.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens above 24,750; BSE Sensex over 200 points up

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Dale Steyn broke down in tears after South Africa won the World Test Championship, ending their 27-year wait for an ICC title. The iconic pacer proudly showed his old Test cap and called the moment “incredible,” while fighting back emotion on air.
title: 'Tears, Test cap, and a big thumbs up' – Dale Steyn's raw reaction goes viral

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A Lufthansa flight bound for Hyderabad from Frankfurt was compelled to return to its origin due to a bomb threat received while the aircraft was outside Indian airspace. Initially, passengers were informed that the diversion was due to a denial of landing permission at Hyderabad. Passengers have been provided accommodation and are scheduled to fly out the next morning.
title: 'Bomb threat': Hyd-bound Lufthansa flight forced to return to Germany; 'denied permit to land'

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: ‘Criminal Justice’ Season 4 has viewers hooked, with the mystery surrounding Roshni's murder deepening as Episode 6 approaches. Online, fans are actively sharing theories, with Kamala, the maid, and Ira, Dr. Raj's daughter, emerging as prime suspects. Some even suggest a complex conspiracy involving multiple characters, heightening the suspense as the truth remains elusive.
title: 'Criminal Justice' S4 E6: Who killed Roshni Saluja? Here’s what netizens decode

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Kuldeep Yadav revealed he now occupies Rohit Sharma's seat on the team bus, choosing to sit with Ravindra Jadeja following Sharma's Test retirement and Shubman Gill's captaincy appointment. Kuldeep emphasized his desire to learn from Jadeja, especially with Ashwin's absence.
title: IND vs ENG: 'Uspe main baithta hun'; Kuldeep takes over Rohit's bus seat

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has alleged that Iran views Donald Trump as its primary adversary and even plotted his assassination. He lauded Trump's firm stance against Iran's nuclear ambitions, citing actions like Soleimani's killing. Netanyahu, describing himself as Trump's ally, warned of an imminent nuclear threat to Israel, defending Operation Rising Lion as crucial in hindering Iran's nuclear progress.
title: 'Iran wants to kill Trump': Israel PM Netanyahu makes shock claim

author: SUDIPTA SENGUPTA
description: Hyderabad's Old City sees a rise in undocumented contract marriages. Poor Muslim women are often abandoned without legal recourse. Victims lack proof of marriage, leaving them vulnerable. Decriminalization of adultery and ban on triple talaq contribute to this trend. Marriage bureaus arrange these illegal unions for commission. Women are left with no support after being deserted by their husbands.
title: Khutbah shaadi: 'Married' without papers, dumped without scruples

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Beyond alcohol, many daily habits silently harm your liver. Excessive sugar intake, even from seemingly healthy sources, and a sedentary lifestyle contribute to liver damage. Overuse of painkillers, crash diets, and artificial sweeteners also pose risks. Prioritizing hydration, mindful supplement use, stress management, sufficient sleep, and moderate alcohol consumption are crucial for liver health.
title: Liver health: 10 everyday habits that are slowly damaging it without you knowing

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ahead of the Test series against England, Shubman Gill reflected on Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma's captaincy styles. Gill praised Rohit's aggressive tactics and clear communication, highlighting his ability to be firm yet approachable. He admired Kohli's proactive thinking and adaptability on the field.
title: Shubman Gill discusses Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's captaincy style

author: HARVEER DABAS
description: In Uttar Pradesh's Amroha district, a 50-year-old farmer is in critical condition after a snake bit his tongue while he attempted to kiss it for a video. The incident occurred when Jitendra Kumar, reportedly intoxicated, rescued the snake and tried to film a stunt. He is currently in the ICU, with villagers confirming the incident.
title: UP man tries to kiss snake for reel, gets bitten; in ICU

author: PARTH SHASTRI
description: On June 12th at 1.40 pm, Satinder Singh Sandhu of EMRI 108 responded to a loud explosion near Civil Hospital. Arriving quickly, his team aided the injured hostel guard and Ramesh Viswashkumar, the sole survivor who was desperately searching for his brother amidst the chaos. The EMRI 108 team ensured Viswashkumar's safe transport to Civil Hospital.
title: Air India crash: Survivor tried to go back to save brother, says first responder

author: SIDHARTHA
description: Soon, Indians can share Aadhaar electronically via a QR code-based app, eliminating the need for photocopies. UIDAI plans to accept documents like birth certificates and driving licenses for address updates, reducing fraud and the need to visit Aadhaar centers. CEO Bhuvnesh Kumar announced the new app, enabling most updates from home, excluding biometrics.
title: E-Aadhaar: You’ll soon be able to do everything sitting at home, says UIDAI CEO

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Former NASA agent Joseph Gutheinz dismisses UFO sightings as alien visits, citing vast interstellar distances. He suggests these sightings are likely advanced drones, secret military tech, or government cover-ups to conceal projects from adversaries. Gutheinz urges rational thinking, demanding evidence and suggesting a focus on earthly explanations rather than extraterrestrial speculation.
title: Ex-NASA agent debunks UFO theories, says government used them to ‘hide a lot of things’

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: 'Get the job done': Trump orders US agencies to crack down on illegal aliens

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: The Indiana Pacers are evaluating Myles Turner's future after inconsistent playoff performances, potentially opening the door for a trade. A proposed deal involves the Dallas Mavericks sending Dereck Lively II to Indiana for Bennedict Mathurin. This move could provide the Pacers with a younger, more versatile center, while Dallas would gain a promising scorer to develop.
title: NBA rumours: Mavericks eye Pacers star in offseason shake-up; Myles Turner or Mathurin key todeal?

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A filmmaker's family in New Delhi submitted DNA samples after he disappeared near the Air India crash site in Ahmedabad. His last known location was 700 meters from where the plane crashed shortly after takeoff, killing 270. His wife reported his phone switched off around the time of the crash, and his usual route home was not taken.
title: 'Was 700 metres away from site': Filmmaker missing since AI crash

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: Google is reportedly cutting ties with Scale AI after Meta's significant investment, raising data security concerns among major clients like Microsoft and xAI. These companies fear proprietary data exposure to a competitor. Google, initially planning a $200 million payment to Scale this year, is actively shifting its workload to rivals, potentially impacting Scale's operations.
title: Funding fallout: Mark Zuckerberg backs ScaleAI; Google, Microsoft & others quietly step away

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Three Foxconn employees faced prison sentences for leaking iPad 2 design details to Shenzhen MacTop Electronics before its release. In exchange for digital images, MacTop offered money and product discounts, gaining a competitive advantage in accessory production. Apple's aggressive stance on secrecy persists despite ongoing leaks due to its vast supply chain.
title: Security crackdown: China jails three for leaking unreleased Apple gadget

author: BHARAT YAGNIK
description: Following the AI 171 crash, authorities faced significant hurdles in notifying families due to a lack of emergency contact information. In a staggering 70% of cases, the only number available was the passenger's, hindering immediate communication. This forced officials to rely on local administrators to locate and inform relatives, causing delays and complicating support efforts during a critical time.
title: Ahmedabad plane crash: Not emergency contacts, most flyers had listed own numbers

author: KANGKAN KALITA
description: Tensions flared in Manipur as Kuki and Meitei villagers clashed over ploughing rights near Sadu Lampak, along the Imphal East-Kangpokpi border. The dispute arose when a Meitei farmer attempted to cultivate land, leading to objections from Kuki villagers. Minor injuries were reported, and security forces intervened.
title: Farmers' stand-off near Manipur's ethnic buffer zone

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Tarun Mansukhani's comedy 'Housefull 5,' starring Akshay Kumar, Abhishek Bachchan, and Riteish Deshmukh, continues its box office reign, crossing ₹150 crore in India within ten days. The film witnessed a significant boost during its second weekend, collecting ₹11 crore on Sunday, June 15, 2025. Its total collection stands at ₹153.
title: 'Housefull 5' BO collection: Akshay Kumar's film surpasses Rs 150 cr mark

author: PATHIKRIT CHAKRABORTY
description: Home Minister Amit Shah lauded Uttar Pradesh's record-breaking police recruitment drive, hiring over 60,000 constables, including a significant number of women. He emphasized the transparency of the selection process, highlighting merit-based appointments and the absence of bias, contrasting it with previous administrations.
title: Shah praise for CM Yogi on hiring record 60k constables 'sans bias'

author: SAURABH SINHA AND GAURAV TALWAR
description: A surge in helicopter accidents, including two fatal crashes, has put Kedarnath's pilgrimage route under scrutiny. Pilots cite unpredictable weather, lack of air traffic control, and pressure to maintain flight schedules as major safety concerns.
title: Uttarakhand chopper crash: No radar, no rules; inside Kedarnath's risky circuit

author: TNN
description: Ramesh Bhaliya arrived in Ahmedabad to claim his younger son Ajaykumar's remains after the AI 171 plane crash, while his elder son Viswash, the sole survivor, recovers in the hospital. The brothers, British citizens originally from Diu, were in India for business. Viswash, seated near the emergency exit, survived while Ajaykumar perished shortly after takeoff.
title: Air India crash: He flew to Ahmedabad to say hello to one son, goodbye to another

author: TNN
description: Following the Air India Flight 171 crash on June 12, authorities have identified and released the bodies of 38 victims to their families, including former Gujarat CM Vijay Rupani. DNA matching is ongoing to identify remaining victims, with 86 passengers and crew matched by Sunday evening.
title: Air India plane crash: Bodies of 38 victims handed to kin; Rupani among those IDed

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: Airspace closures following the Ahmedabad crash and enhanced Dreamliner checks are causing significant flight delays. Air India faces increased flying times and turnaround times, leading to cancellations. Dubai's air traffic control is overwhelmed, impacting various airlines, including SpiceJet, and leaving passengers stranded, with Dubai Airports issuing advisories about cancellations and delays.
title: Airspace closures, Dreamliner checks trigger delays

author: BV SHIVASHANKAR
description: Karnataka's Congress government faces a dilemma over a new caste survey, sparking discontent among OBCs who fear losing advantages from the un-implemented Kantharaj Commission report, which favored them. Lingayats and Vokkaligas, who opposed the previous report, are planning their own surveys. The government aims to complete the new survey in 90 days, following Congress leadership's directive.
title: CM Siddaramaiah sandwiched as anti-caste survey agitation brews in Karnataka

author: GAURAV TALWAR
description: Kedarnath's helicopter operations, vital for the yatra, face high risks due to the absence of air traffic control, radar coverage, and real-time weather monitoring. Pilots navigate the challenging air corridor relying on visual cues, raising safety concerns. Despite past accidents and proposed safety measures, critical infrastructure gaps persist, leaving flights vulnerable to unpredictable weather conditions.
title: New rules after 2022 crash still fall short of international norms: Experts

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Amid escalating military strikes between Iran and Israel, US President Donald Trump urged both nations to negotiate a deal, acknowledging potential continued conflict beforehand. Recent clashes mark a dangerous escalation, with direct strikes replacing proxy warfare, raising concerns of a broader Middle East war. Trump hinted at behind-the-scenes efforts towards peace, expressing optimism for a future agreement.
title: 'Sometimes they have to fight it out': Trump says Iran-Israel will fight before peace

author: SIDHARTHA
description: India and the US are nearing completion of the initial phase of a bilateral trade agreement, aiming to finalize the text before July 9. India is considering concessions on agricultural products and automobiles in exchange for a 10% duty on labor-intensive goods like textiles and footwear.
title: India, US close to finalising 'early tranche' of trade deal
